dct_description_sm: U.S. Coast and Geodetic Survey ; H.S. Pritchett, superintendent ; verified: O.H. Tittman, assistant in charge of the Office ; Gershom Bradford ... hydrographic inspector.
"Topography by A.M. Harrison and W.E. Greenwell ... between 1852 and 1878. Hydrography by Ed Cordell ... and G. Farquhar ... in 1869."
Relief shown by contours and spot heights; depths shown by soundings.
Also shows drainage, topographical features, and settlements.
Includes notes on soundings, tides, lighthouses, and elevations.
